## New violations in PR #23 — analysis

The three moderate violations that appear only in PR #23's Scorer page are **environment artifacts**:

| Rule ID | Target | Why it fires |
|---------|--------|-------------|
| `landmark-one-main` | `<html>` | The Scorer loaded into the `#no-config` empty state (no scorer data found) |
| `page-has-heading-one` | `<html>` | Same — the `#no-config` UI has no `<h1>` |
| `region` | `#no-config` | Same — orphaned content in empty state |

**Root cause:** Vercel preview deployments start with empty localStorage. The demo scorer `demo-written-response-v2` is stored in the browser's local storage on production, so `scorer.html?id=demo-written-response-v2` loads the full scoring UI there. On the fresh Vercel preview domain, no such data exists, so the page renders the "no scorer found" fallback UI instead.

PR #23's one-line change (`bg-white/90 backdrop-blur` → `bg-white`) is confined to the rail CSS — it has no path to the `#no-config` state. These violations are pre-existing in the no-config state and are definitively **not introduced by PR #23**.

