## True violations vs compositing-sensitive note

The 4 rail nodes that failed on production were **compositing-sensitive**, not straightforwardly true violations:
- Local axe filed them as `incomplete / needs review` (matching the PR #23 description)
- The external automated setup resolved the `rgba(255,255,255,0.90)` backdrop composite to an effective background darker than white, producing a marginal fail
- The fix (opaque `bg-white`) makes the background deterministic for every tool and removes the ambiguity entirely

The 3 Scorer violations in PR #23 (`landmark-one-main`, `page-has-heading-one`, `region`) are **environment artifacts** with no bearing on the actual scoring interface.

